						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="41r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Kavanot ha-filosofim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">כונות הפילוסופים</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31996761">Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31996761">אלע'זאלי, מחמד בן מחמד</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Part 1 and a portion of part 2 (beginning on folio 25r) of the anonymous Hebrew translation of Ghazzali's Kavanot ha-pilosofim, with Moses Narboni's commentary.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="41r" to="55r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ha-gedarim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">הגדרים</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/251093020">Bonafos, Menahem ben Abraham</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/251093020">פרפיניאן, מנחם בן אברהם</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The text was apparently copied from the printed edition of Salonica, 1567.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="55r" to="72v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ha-she᾿elah ṿeha-teshuvah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">השאלה והתשובה</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/236618079">Yehudah ben Binyamin ibn Ruksh</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/236618079">רוקש, יהודה בן בנימין</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>A response of ibn Ruksh to an inquiry of his father Binyamin regarding the three angels who appeared to Abraham. The response consists of 42 chapters and takes a form of philosophical exposition of the relevant biblical passages.</p>
								<p>From folio 63v onwards, the scribe copied parts of Ginze ha-melekh by Yitsḥaḳ ibn Latif, perhaps from the New York JTS MS 2383, folios 60r- 71v.</p>
								<p>See further Kreisel, Kiryat sefer 62, pp. 439-447.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נכתב על ידי <name type="person" role="scribe">יחזקאל בן כ"ה שמואל כהן</name>
